; maize-14: mzdis reserved/unassigned-opcode-byte resync fixture (AC6481).
;
; HALT, then two reserved bytes ($21, $93 -- both explicitly "reserved" per
; README.md:1146,1260) embedded via DATA (a raw byte literal, not an
; instruction), then a valid instruction (NOP), then HALT. mzdis must decode
; each reserved byte as its own "DB $XX ; unknown opcode" line, advancing
; exactly one byte each time, and resume correct decoding at NOP.

HALT
DATA $21
DATA $93
NOP
HALT
